Subject: Enable mutter X11 backend (Ubuntu 26.04)

Enable the mutter X11 backend (Meson `-Dx11=true`) so GNOME Shell can run as a
real X11 window manager/compositor in an "Ubuntu on Xorg" session.

This patch also installs `mutter-restart-helper` (produced when building with
X11 enabled) and updates the `libmutter-17-0` symbols file for the additional
X11-related exported symbols.

